Posts.Content: http://www.prostatecancer.org.in Rates of prostate cancer vary widely across the world. It is least common in South and East Asia, more common in Europe - though the rates vary widely between countries - and most common in the United States. According to the American Cancer Society, prostate cancer is least common among Asian men and most common among black men with figures for European men in between . However, these high rates may be affected by increasing rates of detection .
